Steps to perform an out-of-source build of gtest libraries.


-->  Create a build directory, copy configure.sh to it, and move to it

%> cd $HOME/DAGMC/gtest   // the directory of this README
%> mkdir bld
%> cp configure.sh bld
%> cd bld

-->  Export a definition of GTEST_DIR, the directory containing CMakeLists.txt

%> export GTEST_DIR=$HOME/DAGMC/gtest/gtest-1.7.0

--> Run the cmake script

%> ./configure.sh

--> Upon successful completion, copy the library one level up

%> cp libgtest.a ..


Now the fludag tests can be compiled

NOTE:  This documentation needs updating
